The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 1: The government may selectively extend more sops to exporters rather than withdraw the stimulus given to them last year in the face of the global slowdown, commerce minister Anand Sharma has said. The engineering sector may need some support. For apparel and handicrafts, we will see if we can do something more. We will review and see if we can give some more incentives, Sharma said.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 1: The empowered committee of state finance ministers will submit its first draft to the Centre on the proposed goods and services tax next week, undeterred by speculations that the implementation of the new tax regime may be delayed.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 1: The power sector will require an investment of about $250 billion (about Rs 12,50,000 crore) in the next eight years for its growth, a CII-AT Kearney study said, highlighting emerging opportunities in future electricity markets.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 1: The government has asked the Serious Fraud Investigation Office to discontinue its enquiry into the misuse of funds by Satyam Computer to avoid duplication of work as the CBI is already trailing the funds parked abroad by the IT firm.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 1: NTPC today started receiving natural gas from Reliance Industries eastern offshore KG-D6 fields at the government-approved price of $4.20 per mmBtu.                                                                                                                           
